  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">UG-2065 EDU Active Learning Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EDU Active Learning Project contains a learning resource (Correctbook) that helps learners to practice basic skills (e.g. in writing, maths, art) and carry out application and problem solving tasks individually and together. It provides new opportunities to train teachers and reach learners at STAR schools, reach new schools, offer third parties a partnership possibility and practice training on digital platforms. 
The training programme is structured in 3 steps: 
1. Train Master-trainers to lay the basis for what needs to be done in the countries. 
2. Master trainers train teacher trainers on how to train and support teachers to use Correctbook. 
3. Training of teachers, the actual users of Correctbook. 
All trainings are co-constructive rather than descriptive by nature. In order to reach our aims EDU-ALP trainers and partners from each country must be able to apply and contextualise the contents for their own contexts.</narrative>
  </description>
